1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a new approach for generating bounding box proposals, which is a core component in many computer vision tasks. 2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed approach utilizes a CNN-based category agnostic object location refinement module, which can be considered as an AI technique. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an active strategy for generating box proposals that starts from a set of seed boxes and progressively moves its attention on the promising image areas, which can be considered as a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed approach can be applied to robotics tasks that involve object detection and localization. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper evaluates the proposed approach on several multimedia datasets, including COCO, PASCAL, ImageNet detection, and NYU-Depth V2 datasets.
